# Rails Test And CI Commands

When running Rails commands from the agent environment:

- Use `env -u BUNDLE_PATH bundle exec rails test ...` for Rails tests.
- Tests that need the local MySQL socket may need to run outside the sandbox.
- `bin/brakeman` injects `--ensure-latest`; if CI fails only with "Brakeman X is not the latest version Y", update `Gemfile.lock`.
- Verify Brakeman with `env -u BUNDLE_PATH bin/brakeman --no-pager`.
- Do not change `bin/brakeman` to bypass the latest-version policy.
